<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                        <head>597. Telegram 41 from Geneva to Prague<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d597fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/5–856. Confidential; Limit Distribution. Repeated to the
                                Department of State as telegram 1855 and to Warsaw as telegram
                                7.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-05-08">May 8, 1956, 4
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d597-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d597-1"/>
                        <p>41. From Osborn.</p>
                        <p>Warsaw’s 20 to Geneva repeated information Department 797 notes new
                            Polish Foreign Minister reception May 8. Believe this adequately
                            explains postponement. No record here <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName>s having arrived by air past week.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>